00:04:17,540 --> 00:04:25,880
♫ When the cold wind blows, it makes me realize who is warm ♫

31
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:33,200
♫ When the cold wind passes,
it makes you know who your heart misses ♫

32
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:36,730
♫ It's still that person ♫

33
00:04:37,930 --> 00:04:40,160
♫ That one person ♫

34
00:04:41,850 --> 00:04:46,270
♫ That one person ♫

35
00:04:46,270 --> 00:04:49,500
♫ That one person ♫

36
00:04:50,930 --> 00:04:57,100
♫ And the cold wind still hasn't taken you out of my mind ♫

37
00:04:59,320 --> 00:05:06,430
[Second Chance: The Series]

38
00:05:14,019 --> 00:05:15,919
How is he?

39
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:19,060
Take a seat.

40
00:05:24,670 --> 00:05:27,110
How's he doing?

41
00:05:29,580 --> 00:05:33,520
Well, as you can see...

42
00:05:34,660 --> 00:05:38,600
The doctor said he's getting better though.

43
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:45,300
And... you?

44
00:05:45,300 --> 00:05:46,906
How are you doing?

45
00:05:46,906 --> 00:05:48,706
I'm okay.

46
00:05:52,150 --> 00:05:57,650
Have you eaten anything? You look exhausted.

47
00:05:58,970 --> 00:06:00,670
I'm not hungry.

48
00:06:00,670 --> 00:06:05,460
Hey, at this rate you'll die before Tong Fah.

49
00:06:06,330 --> 00:06:08,070
I'm not in the mood for eating.

50
00:06:08,070 --> 00:06:12,559
I'll go get you something to eat. I'll be right back.

51
00:06:12,559 --> 00:06:16,360
No, thanks. I'll grab it myself later.

52
00:06:16,360 --> 00:06:22,179
As if! Just wait here, I'll go grab it real quick.

53
00:06:22,179 --> 00:06:24,080
I'll be right back.

54
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:42,160
Is something bothering you?

55
00:06:44,140 --> 00:06:45,990
About that...

56
00:06:45,990 --> 00:06:50,130
If somebody confesses to you at the school canteen,

57
00:06:50,130 --> 00:06:52,250
how would you feel?

58
00:06:55,550 --> 00:06:57,730
Happy, I guess?

59
00:07:00,550 --> 00:07:04,550
Being liked is better than being hated, isn't it?

60
00:07:09,830 --> 00:07:12,030
I...

61
00:07:12,030 --> 00:07:16,630
I got beaten nearly to death by that bastard Arthur before,

62
00:07:17,830 --> 00:07:21,030
when we were dating. You remember?

63
00:07:21,030 --> 00:07:23,510
It was really awful.

64
00:07:23,510 --> 00:07:29,410
So I didn't want to be with anyone anymore.

65
00:07:29,410 --> 00:07:33,210
At least I won't get hurt if I'm alone.

66
00:07:36,630 --> 00:07:39,230
Yeah, I get you.

67
00:07:39,230 --> 00:07:41,790
I was scared too.

68
00:07:41,790 --> 00:07:44,870
I ran away from my feelings.

69
00:07:44,870 --> 00:07:50,790
I was scared because there is always an end to a beginning.

70
00:07:53,110 --> 00:07:55,649
Look what my fear has cost me.

71
00:07:55,649 --> 00:07:58,690
I almost lost the most important person in my life.

72
00:08:07,190 --> 00:08:13,070
Listen... To love is better than to hate.

73
00:08:13,070 --> 00:08:16,990
Stop putting up defenses and open your heart.

74
00:08:16,990 --> 00:08:20,510
Who knows? You might be missing the most important thing in your life.

75
00:08:22,090 --> 00:08:27,329
Life is short. If you like somebody, just go for it.

76
00:08:27,329 --> 00:08:31,870
If you don't like that person, just say no.

77
00:08:31,870 --> 00:08:34,050
Do what you want to do.

78
00:08:34,050 --> 00:08:36,970
Don't shut yourself out.

79
00:08:36,970 --> 00:08:38,950
You get what I'm saying, right?

80
00:08:48,530 --> 00:08:53,470
Okay. I'll think about it.

81
00:08:59,550 --> 00:09:02,869
One, two. One, two.

82
00:09:02,869 --> 00:09:05,069
One, two! Harder!

83
00:09:05,069 --> 00:09:07,589
Quick! Harder!

84
00:09:08,830 --> 00:09:10,700
Do you need a break?

85
00:09:10,710 --> 00:09:13,330
Why can't you focus at all?

86
00:09:13,330 --> 00:09:15,629
Are you all right?

87
00:09:15,629 --> 00:09:17,590
Go take a break first.

88
00:09:18,830 --> 00:09:20,630
I'm sorry.

89
00:09:23,670 --> 00:09:25,940
What's wrong?

90
00:09:27,780 --> 00:09:30,690
You can't seem to focus at all.

91
00:09:37,270 --> 00:09:40,549
Is Jeno not coming today?

92
00:09:40,550 --> 00:09:42,850
No, he's not.

93
00:09:56,050 --> 00:09:57,829
Where should we sit?

94
00:09:57,830 --> 00:10:00,069
Just anywhere.

95
00:10:00,070 --> 00:10:02,330
Let's sit over there then.

96
00:10:03,550 --> 00:10:06,189
Hey, let's get out of here.

97
00:10:06,189 --> 00:10:08,069
What? Why?

98
00:10:08,070 --> 00:10:10,149
Everyone's looking at us.

99
00:10:10,150 --> 00:10:14,070
I'm sure they're all talking about me.

100
00:10:14,070 --> 00:10:16,510
I'm sure it's nothing.

101
00:10:19,710 --> 00:10:22,570
Gosh, what's wrong with you?

102
00:10:22,570 --> 00:10:25,970
You're acting like a fugitive.

103
00:10:25,970 --> 00:10:28,370
That's not it.

104
00:10:28,370 --> 00:10:32,330
Is Arthur following you?

105
00:10:33,550 --> 00:10:35,910
No.

106
00:10:35,910 --> 00:10:38,240
Then, what's the matter?

107
00:10:40,670 --> 00:10:44,760
Look around. Everyone's looking at me.

108
00:10:47,449 --> 00:10:53,770
They're probably talking about how Chris confessed to me here.

109
00:10:58,130 --> 00:11:00,050
What should I do?

110
00:11:02,070 --> 00:11:07,349
Jeno, just ignore those people and forget about it.

111
00:11:09,830 --> 00:11:11,929
Listen to me.

112
00:11:11,929 --> 00:11:15,250
You can't control how other people think about you.

113
00:11:15,250 --> 00:11:21,350
So just let it go and do whatever makes you happy.

114
00:11:21,350 --> 00:11:26,969
And it's exam period now, so there is no one who is so free to care about that anymore.

115
00:11:33,890 --> 00:11:37,950
Why are you so down? This isn't like you, Chris.

116
00:11:43,250 --> 00:11:47,220
There's always a way out.

117
00:11:47,220 --> 00:11:49,330
Don't give up yet.

118
00:11:49,330 --> 00:11:53,270
I'm always here by your side.

119
00:11:54,590 --> 00:11:56,290
Thanks a lot.

120
00:11:57,670 --> 00:11:59,810
How's your friend doing by the way?

121
00:11:59,810 --> 00:12:02,270
Bitch! He's your friend, too.

122
00:12:02,270 --> 00:12:03,870
That hurts!

123
00:12:09,710 --> 00:12:11,510
I miss him.

124
00:12:12,970 --> 00:12:15,469
Yeah, me too.

125
00:12:15,470 --> 00:12:21,309
You're lying. You only visited him once after he got hospitalized.

126
00:12:21,309 --> 00:12:24,710
I was occupied.

127
00:12:30,190 --> 00:12:32,550
Let's go eat something.

128
00:12:42,770 --> 00:12:45,020
Let me help.

129
00:12:45,020 --> 00:12:52,010
[Second Chance: The Series]

130
00:13:01,930 --> 00:13:03,830
Let me help.

131
00:13:14,490 --> 00:13:17,050
Don't be scared. I'm not going to hurt you.

132
00:13:19,490 --> 00:13:22,750
So many books. Isn't it heavy?

133
00:13:23,650 --> 00:13:25,860
What do you want?

134
00:13:26,650 --> 00:13:30,750
You disappeared for so long, and now you're here.

135
00:13:30,750 --> 00:13:32,970
What do you want from me?

136
00:13:37,970 --> 00:13:40,170
I just wanted to make up.

137
00:13:42,790 --> 00:13:45,110
I said no.

138
00:13:48,330 --> 00:13:52,930
I'm sorry. I'll do anything.

139
00:13:54,170 --> 00:13:56,670
Can we please get back together?

140
00:13:58,970 --> 00:14:00,950
Let go.

141
00:14:06,410 --> 00:14:08,970
I said let go!

142
00:14:27,970 --> 00:14:29,570
Does it hurt?

143
00:14:30,650 --> 00:14:33,270
Of course, it hurts.

144
00:14:34,110 --> 00:14:36,489
You still like Jeno?

145
00:14:36,490 --> 00:14:38,210
No.

146
00:14:39,690 --> 00:14:41,830
I just wanted to get revenge on Chris.

147
00:14:49,690 --> 00:14:52,570
Hey, about Near...

148
00:14:52,570 --> 00:14:53,870
What about him?

149
00:14:53,870 --> 00:14:56,749
I really don't want to say this.

150
00:14:56,749 --> 00:14:59,529
Oh, come on. Just say it already.

151
00:14:59,530 --> 00:15:06,149
He clearly doesn't know how to work and he's always late.

152
00:15:06,149 --> 00:15:09,909
I find him very irresponsible.

153
00:15:09,909 --> 00:15:14,089
I know, right? I've seen him coming late many times, but he never gets in trouble.

154
00:15:14,089 --> 00:15:17,350
While I got in trouble when I was late only twice.

155
00:15:17,350 --> 00:15:20,650
Well, he's got connections.

156
00:15:20,650 --> 00:15:24,190
No wonder he has a job here.

157
00:15:24,190 --> 00:15:30,689
If it wasn't Em, he wouldn't even be working here.

158
00:15:30,689 --> 00:15:34,890
Oh, now I get it. He has Em supporting him all the time,

159
00:15:34,890 --> 00:15:37,670
no wonder he can work shamelessly.

160
00:15:40,330 --> 00:15:43,910
What are you guys talking about?

161
00:15:43,910 --> 00:15:47,190
Oh, just something in general.

162
00:15:57,010 --> 00:15:59,050
Mind if I ask you something?

163
00:16:00,450 --> 00:16:02,190
Go ahead.

164
00:16:03,610 --> 00:16:10,010
Were you the one who accepted me for this job even if I wasn't the right fit for it?

165
00:16:10,010 --> 00:16:13,390
What? No, it's not like that.

166
00:16:13,390 --> 00:16:18,329
Do I look that pathetic to you?

167
00:16:18,330 --> 00:16:24,270
Near, listen. I didn't mean to deceive you.

168
00:16:25,590 --> 00:16:29,329
Oh, yeah? You didn't mean to deceive me?

169
00:16:29,330 --> 00:16:31,820
But you already lied to me about two things.

170
00:16:32,540 --> 00:16:36,490
About the game and this.

171
00:16:40,050 --> 00:16:43,610
I am sorry. I really didn't mean to.

172
00:16:43,610 --> 00:16:45,210
Please believe me.

173
00:16:53,060 --> 00:16:56,040
If I didn't hear them talking,

174
00:16:56,049 --> 00:17:00,530
I still wouldn't have known. Why did you do this?

175
00:17:03,490 --> 00:17:06,010
I was going to tell you.

176
00:17:06,010 --> 00:17:10,430
But I couldn't find the right timing.

177
00:17:12,210 --> 00:17:16,589
So if you can't find the right timing, were you intending to not tell me at all?

178
00:17:16,589 --> 00:17:18,600
No, it's not like that.

179
00:17:18,600 --> 00:17:21,160
I'll just leave now.

180
00:18:59,250 --> 00:19:01,290
Hold on!

181
00:19:01,290 --> 00:19:02,510
What?

182
00:19:02,510 --> 00:19:05,580
Stop messing around with my brother.

183
00:19:05,589 --> 00:19:08,510
Why do I have to listen to you?

184
00:19:08,510 --> 00:19:11,089
If you don't stop,

185
00:19:11,089 --> 00:19:14,569
I'll be telling the whole school about you cheating on your exam.

186
00:19:14,570 --> 00:19:17,969
- The whole school.
- The whole school.

187
00:19:21,110 --> 00:19:26,009
I didn't cheat, and your threatening is not scary at all.

188
00:19:26,009 --> 00:19:28,020
Oh, you sure?

189
00:19:29,050 --> 00:19:33,489
Well, all the evidence is here!

190
00:19:33,489 --> 00:19:38,810
Sure! If you want to try us, fine! Bring it on!

191
00:19:47,010 --> 00:19:48,780
You better brace yourself.

192
00:19:48,780 --> 00:19:51,210
I'm going to make you pay for this.

193
00:19:51,210 --> 00:19:53,789
- Bring it on!
- Bye.

194
00:19:53,789 --> 00:19:57,089
- Bye.
- I'll be waiting.
- Pull yourself together!

195
00:19:57,089 --> 00:19:58,610
Let's go.

196
00:19:59,930 --> 00:20:03,809
- Bye.
- Bye-bye.
- Bye.

197
00:20:07,930 --> 00:20:09,009
That was close.

198
00:20:09,010 --> 00:20:10,910
Super scary.

199
00:20:10,910 --> 00:20:13,670
My face got all stiff.

200
00:20:13,670 --> 00:20:17,889
My legs were shaking so much that I thought they'd notice me being scared.

201
00:20:19,270 --> 00:20:23,110
They are more stupid than I thought!

202
00:20:23,110 --> 00:20:24,950
Yes, super stupid.

203
00:20:24,950 --> 00:20:27,570
Just a fake thumb drive.

204
00:20:33,010 --> 00:20:35,030
Oh my god, too much.

205
00:20:36,470 --> 00:20:39,250
- Did you see her just now?
- Yes.

206
00:20:50,950 --> 00:20:53,250
Hello.

207
00:20:53,250 --> 00:20:55,209
You're still here, huh?

208
00:20:55,210 --> 00:20:57,210
Yeah.

209
00:21:17,250 --> 00:21:20,610
Have you made up your mind about your studies?

210
00:21:22,710 --> 00:21:24,930
No, not really.

211
00:21:25,710 --> 00:21:28,369
And I don't want to think about it.

212
00:21:28,369 --> 00:21:30,110
Why?

213
00:21:31,210 --> 00:21:36,030
There are so many things going on right now that I don't want more.

214
00:21:45,850 --> 00:21:49,830
You want to tell me something? I'm here to listen.

215
00:22:03,090 --> 00:22:07,480
If you confessed to a person

216
00:22:07,480 --> 00:22:09,710
and that person is unhappy about it,

217
00:22:09,710 --> 00:22:11,470
what would you do?

218
00:22:14,050 --> 00:22:16,210
Oh, so it was a love issue?

219
00:22:16,210 --> 00:22:18,950
I thought you were struggling with something else.

220
00:22:23,950 --> 00:22:27,930
Have you heard "to love is to give?"

221
00:22:29,710 --> 00:22:33,340
Well, if you already gave that person what you had,

222
00:22:33,340 --> 00:22:36,870
I think that it's already good enough.

223
00:22:37,670 --> 00:22:43,689
That person liking you back or not, that's up to that person.

224
00:22:43,690 --> 00:22:45,560
So don't stress about it.

225
00:22:45,560 --> 00:22:48,270
It's not like you can do something about it.

226
00:22:49,730 --> 00:22:51,871
I see. But...

227
00:22:51,871 --> 00:22:55,290
But you still want that person to like you back, right?

228
00:22:59,790 --> 00:23:02,310
Then keep fighting.

229
00:23:02,310 --> 00:23:07,390
Prove to that person that you really mean it.

230
00:23:08,790 --> 00:23:11,150
Do you think it'll work?

231
00:23:16,450 --> 00:23:20,550
Well, it's going to take some time.

232
00:23:22,450 --> 00:23:28,150
Sometimes, these things depend on some special "chances."

233
00:23:29,610 --> 00:23:35,330
So good luck in finding that "second chance."

234
00:23:38,930 --> 00:23:42,850
Thank you. I'll give it a try.

235
00:23:47,290 --> 00:23:51,750
Are you playing alone? Mind if I join you?

236
00:23:52,990 --> 00:23:54,929
Oh, sure.

237
00:23:54,929 --> 00:23:57,449
You know I'm a damn pro at this.

238
00:23:57,450 --> 00:23:58,950
Let's go.

239
00:24:04,460 --> 00:24:11,380
[Second Chance: The Series]

240
00:24:30,510 --> 00:24:32,110
Near.

241
00:24:36,990 --> 00:24:40,350
I am sorry about what happened yesterday.

242
00:24:41,770 --> 00:24:44,070
Can we please talk?

243
00:24:47,510 --> 00:24:49,790
You want to talk?

244
00:24:54,230 --> 00:24:56,530
What do you think I am?

245
00:24:58,870 --> 00:25:01,110
Why didn't you tell me the truth?

246
00:25:04,610 --> 00:25:07,330
I didn't mean to not tell you.

247
00:25:11,390 --> 00:25:14,290
I just couldn't find the right timing.

248
00:25:16,450 --> 00:25:21,850
You knew about it... from the beginning.

249
00:25:23,450 --> 00:25:25,730
Both, about the game and this.

250
00:25:26,530 --> 00:25:29,070
But you chose to remain silent.

251
00:25:29,890 --> 00:25:35,050
Because I knew you'd be like this, that's why I didn't tell you.

252
00:25:36,790 --> 00:25:40,849
I know what kind of person you are.

253
00:25:41,550 --> 00:25:44,110
What you have gone through.

254
00:25:45,790 --> 00:25:48,190
So I didn't tell you.

255
00:25:48,190 --> 00:25:54,890
Because I knew if I told you, you'd react this way.

256
00:25:56,990 --> 00:26:03,169
This is the reason why I chose to get close to you on the game.

257
00:26:04,250 --> 00:26:11,050
Because I know that I cannot do that in real life.

258
00:26:14,550 --> 00:26:19,790
I am sorry if I hurt your feelings.

259
00:26:21,390 --> 00:26:25,570
I didn't expect it to be like this.

260
00:26:30,470 --> 00:26:36,030
If you're uncomfortable seeing me around...

261
00:26:45,430 --> 00:26:48,630
Yes, I don't want to see you.

262
00:26:48,630 --> 00:26:50,130
Near...

263
00:27:12,860 --> 00:27:15,230
[MuayThai Martial Arts]

264
00:27:29,090 --> 00:27:31,690
Oh, hey, you're back.

265
00:27:31,690 --> 00:27:33,370
Yeah.

266
00:27:33,370 --> 00:27:39,500
I ran into Arthur today, and I kind of got scared so...

267
00:27:42,530 --> 00:27:45,590
Can you teach me today?

268
00:27:45,590 --> 00:27:47,170
Of course.

269
00:27:51,890 --> 00:27:55,209
What's wrong? You're being weird.

270
00:27:55,210 --> 00:27:59,430
No, nothing. Isn't this normal?

271
00:28:00,390 --> 00:28:04,100
I mean, you're oddly quiet and still.

272
00:28:04,100 --> 00:28:08,130
Normally, you'd be flirty with me.

273
00:28:08,790 --> 00:28:11,570
I thought you didn't like it?

274
00:28:18,370 --> 00:28:20,590
It's so hot today.

275
00:28:24,010 --> 00:28:27,190
So when did you get here?

276
00:28:27,850 --> 00:28:30,030
Right after school.

277
00:28:32,670 --> 00:28:35,450
You're being oddly quiet.

278
00:28:36,530 --> 00:28:40,050
It's not like you at all, Chris.

279
00:28:47,310 --> 00:28:49,409
I'm sorry.

280
00:28:49,409 --> 00:28:57,110
Hey, are you here to train or interview me?

281
00:28:57,890 --> 00:29:00,909
I just want to know.

282
00:29:00,909 --> 00:29:02,890
I'm totally fine.

283
00:29:05,130 --> 00:29:07,850
Are you mad that I rejected you?

284
00:29:15,770 --> 00:29:21,849
I'm not mad. I'm just pulling back.

285
00:29:21,850 --> 00:29:25,510
Because you don't have feelings for me.

286
00:29:31,510 --> 00:29:33,210
You tired?

287
00:29:37,410 --> 00:29:39,570
You hungry?

288
00:29:40,010 --> 00:29:41,790
No.

289
00:29:42,650 --> 00:29:47,749
Then... are you going back home?

290
00:29:47,749 --> 00:29:49,370
Yes.

291
00:29:51,870 --> 00:29:52,869
Why?

292
00:29:52,869 --> 00:29:55,830
Can you give me a ride?

293
00:30:01,170 --> 00:30:03,110
Lead the way.

294
00:30:10,740 --> 00:30:17,470
[Second Chance: The Series]

295
00:30:25,510 --> 00:30:28,229
Hi, I'm Chris. What's your name?

296
00:30:28,229 --> 00:30:31,409
- Jeno.
- What are you waiting for?

297
00:30:31,409 --> 00:30:33,310
Waiting for my sister to come and pick me up.

298
00:30:33,310 --> 00:30:36,049
When is she coming?

299
00:30:36,049 --> 00:30:38,110
She didn't tell me.

300
00:30:38,670 --> 00:30:41,710
Where's your house? I'll take you.

301
00:30:43,790 --> 00:30:46,370
Thank you, Chris.

302
00:30:51,010 --> 00:30:53,790
Thank you. This is my favorite now.

303
00:31:04,670 --> 00:31:06,990
Let's go.

304
00:31:06,990 --> 00:31:08,490
We're going to get caught.

305
00:31:08,490 --> 00:31:10,570
Don't worry.

306
00:31:25,510 --> 00:31:27,150
Sit down.

307
00:31:42,950 --> 00:31:44,970
Do you remember?

308
00:31:47,070 --> 00:31:48,870
Yeah...

309
00:31:50,200 --> 00:31:52,670
I still have the chocolate with me.

310
00:31:53,670 --> 00:31:57,130
I thought you forgot about it already.

311
00:31:58,330 --> 00:32:00,130
No.

312
00:32:00,670 --> 00:32:02,850
I remember everything.

313
00:32:07,950 --> 00:32:13,570
I'm sorry... about that day.

314
00:32:15,710 --> 00:32:17,670
Which day?

315
00:32:19,690 --> 00:32:23,050
The day that I asked you out.

316
00:32:24,430 --> 00:32:29,350
I am really sorry.

317
00:32:30,970 --> 00:32:34,040
Actually... I wasn't embarrassed.

318
00:32:35,350 --> 00:32:38,490
But that was not what I needed.

319
00:32:39,970 --> 00:32:46,650
I just needed a normal love that doesn't stand out.

320
00:32:53,110 --> 00:32:55,730
It's true that I didn't think...

321
00:32:57,830 --> 00:33:00,450
about you at all.

322
00:33:01,110 --> 00:33:05,550
I mean, I didn't consider how you felt.

323
00:33:09,270 --> 00:33:11,190
I am really sorry.

324
00:33:19,350 --> 00:33:22,030
If I thought about it more carefully

325
00:33:23,890 --> 00:33:26,580
and cared more about you,

326
00:33:28,530 --> 00:33:30,430
it would have been better.

327
00:33:34,350 --> 00:33:36,530
I am sorry.

328
00:33:48,230 --> 00:33:53,170
I know you're mad at me, and it's totally understandable.

329
00:33:54,570 --> 00:33:59,300
If you don't want to see me anymore,

330
00:34:01,090 --> 00:34:03,350
feel free to let me know.

331
00:34:05,070 --> 00:34:09,690
I'll go away. I'll disappear from your sight.

332
00:34:12,350 --> 00:34:14,370
You sure you can handle it?

333
00:34:14,930 --> 00:34:16,509
Handle what?

334
00:34:16,509 --> 00:34:20,470
Are you sure that you...

335
00:34:20,470 --> 00:34:24,430
are really okay with that?

336
00:34:35,030 --> 00:34:37,050
Yeah.

337
00:34:39,590 --> 00:34:41,810
But I'm not okay.

338
00:34:58,710 --> 00:35:00,510
Now you're smiling.

339
00:35:23,710 --> 00:35:25,310
Hey!

340
00:35:30,070 --> 00:35:32,050
You're awake?

341
00:35:35,830 --> 00:35:39,610
How are you feeling? Does it hurt anywhere?

342
00:35:41,950 --> 00:35:44,270
Calm down.

343
00:35:45,070 --> 00:35:49,950
It hurts a little but it's fine.

344
00:35:55,150 --> 00:35:57,510
You want some water?

345
00:35:59,930 --> 00:36:01,730
Just a second.

346
00:36:15,830 --> 00:36:17,790
Take it slow.

347
00:36:20,370 --> 00:36:22,510
Drink slowly.

348
00:36:27,730 --> 00:36:29,530
Want more?

349
00:36:40,370 --> 00:36:44,070
You hungry? Do you want to eat anything?

350
00:36:47,070 --> 00:36:48,960
No.

351
00:36:50,420 --> 00:36:53,090
Just seeing you already makes me full.

352
00:36:54,350 --> 00:36:55,970
Yeah, right.

353
00:37:03,590 --> 00:37:05,590
What's wrong?

354
00:37:09,490 --> 00:37:11,590
I missed you.

355
00:37:12,790 --> 00:37:14,850
So, so much.

356
00:37:19,170 --> 00:37:21,470
I was really scared.

357
00:37:25,510 --> 00:37:30,830
I thought I wouldn't be able to see you and talk to you again.

358
00:37:34,710 --> 00:37:37,090
Well, I'm right here.

359
00:37:38,910 --> 00:37:44,070
Don't be scared. I will always be here.

360
00:37:50,610 --> 00:37:53,070
I want to play Jenga.

361
00:37:54,510 --> 00:37:57,290
Let's play it at my place.

362
00:37:58,510 --> 00:38:00,470
Sure.

